text.__SUMMARY__: The St. Thomas beaked snake (Letheobia feae) is a species of snake in the family Typhlopidae.
text.Etymology: The specific name, feae, is in honor of Leonardo Fea, who was an Italian explorer and naturalist.
text.Description: It is found on the island of São Tomé, São Tomé and Príncipe.
text.Further reading: Boulenger GA (1906). "Report on the reptiles collected by the late L. Fea in West Africa". Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, Third Series 2: 196-216. (Typhlops feae, new species, p. 209).
